      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "A field of juvenile debutants suggests a lottery so market moves may prove a crucial guide. Several of these clashed in a trial last week and it was IM FRANKEE (1) that came out on top and she did it in good style. She is by Southwind Frank and hails from the Graham Dwyer stable. The inside draw is an aid to an inexperienced trotter and Cameron Hart sticks with her through that trial win. CHIEF KENNY (6) is a son On A Streak from the Kerryann Morris stable. Draws a little wide but has been performing well at the trials. MAJARO GIRL (4) is a filly by Majestic Son out of a Group 2 winner and is from an accomplished trotting barn in Anton Golino. Has placed in her two most recent trials and should be ready to go. BLESSEDBETHETOOTH (2) is by Father Patrick from the Group 1-winning mare Red Hot Tooth. Should enjoy an economical run from this draw so keep her safe.",
